le> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/24/02 4:35:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Getting box for ring 9 while kos</span><hr size=1> Can it be done?  Usually a quest mob will turn to face you after you say a phrase and get the item.  Pretty sure Sens sees invis so Im assuming I need someone to pull him to zoneline.  Any ideas on this?<br><br>Tobie Baine<br>Assassin<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/25/02 7:30:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting box for ring 9 while kos</span><hr size=1> heh never thought about this....if anything, bring a non-kos cleric and just die. or run for it....if dain isn't up it shouldn't be too hard running from throne room to thurgA with sow or run3. you have nimble disc as well. or bring a mage....have him cast coth, and when there's a few secs left on the coth, do /disc nimble and ask for the box. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulordhavemercy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Have Mercy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/25/02 9:30:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting box for ring 9 while kos</span><hr size=1> he turns real slow, and you can strafe around him and stay sneaking.  thats what i did anyways. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urenbredesanea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Renbre Desanea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/26/02 4:57:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting box for ring 9 while kos</span><hr size=1> just target him and say the phrase while sneaking... he'll turn to you but he surprisingly didnt attack me <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umidibrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Midi Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 9:53:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> did this</span><hr size=1> I did this with my haffling (50 whole sneak skill) warrior while kos.  The trick is to be shrunk, and flatten yourself against the back wall.  You don't have to be BEHIND totally the royal guards. Standing shoulder-shoulder is good enough.<br><br>What you do:  <br>a) Get shrunk<br>b) turn on sneak<br>c) Hide if rogue ( or get someone else to invis if other class)<br>d) get up to the stage<br>e) turn off hide/invis<br>f) get box<br>g) reinvis-hide-group gate<br><br><br>It also really helps to have someone there to hail Seneshal, as he likes to buff everyone and he turns to face them when he does.  Someone on the ground can hail him and keep him facing forwards.<br><br><br>The same tricks can be done to hand in the Giant war helms for +Dain IV faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 1:46:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eureka</span><hr size=1> Ha, figured it out.  Stood in the curtain behind the thone, un hid, waited for hide to refresh, said the phrase and immediately rehid.  Worked like a charm.  Was kind of funny though, I never actuall saw the Sens turn around... /shrug<br><br>Oh well, got ma box and Im happy.<br><br>About the giant helms... give those to the Sens? And how big is the hit?<br><br>Tobie Baine<br>Assassin<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umidibrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Midi Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 2:06:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Helms</span><hr size=1> (OOPS-Not sure on which the name is, but its the cleric mob you hand helms in to, 4 at a time.  Thats Chamberlain correct?  Of course you didnt see Sens turn around, cuase I had a brain fart and was thinking of the Chamerlain.  He does turn around to cast aego and stuff on the guards) <br><br>Do the same thing.  Get shrunk and pressed up against the wall next to the royal guard behind Chamberlain.  Have someone (that can invis, it may help) stand on the floor if front of the Throne to hail Chamberlain, and keep him looking away from you.  Be sure to click off hide or invis (keep sneak on still), and hand in 4 helms at once.  It may look like you are out of range, but you can open a trade window from the back corner of the Thron platform with Chamberlain. They are fairly large sized hits.  It  took me about 10-15 (at 4x helms per) to get out of max-scowls.  And that was with a few Shawl 1 and 2, plus about 80 of the pick sharpening quests ( look up Phenocrysts focus in Wakening Land if you dont know what I am talking about).  That got me to high enough threatening to not be instantly aggroed when unvised, but sneaking to the Royal guards.  <br><br>After that I had to wait about 2 weeks for Dain to finally spawn ( due to all the SoL expansion stuff).  I was able to get up to Dain's bedroom, and behind him to hand in my completed box this way.  Turned off my invis (which I had from my druid after getting a successful sneak on), and handed in all the stuff.  He didnt aggro, and I was very scared.  Also he has 2 royal guards facing into his bedroom.  But I was close enough to dubious, that my aggro range for them was so small they left me alone.  Got my nice red ring.  At this point I should have just gated to GD with my druid.  But instead I stupidly tried to run for it. Dain aggroed and booted me into the pit, and all the golems and terrors ate me.  I was smart enough to run to a spot where nothing spawns to die. Then my druid friend went down there with me, looted my corpse, and gated out.  I had to eat a death, but my 9th ring was very much worth it.<br><br>Of course if you are willing to work faction up a little more slowly, but it HUGE bites, smacking Tormax a couple times will get you enough faction.  I bet 2 will get you out of max-kos.<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umidibrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Midi Brell</A> at: 1/29/02 2:12:13 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3902.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=3902.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3902.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3902.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3902.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3902.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3902.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscuss